Vim-mode nav rework + jump-to-media + tree-toggle hide + jump-last-channel.

Final keymap (vim NORMAL mode):
  j / k         chat line up/down (unchanged)
  Shift+J / K   jump message-by-message in chat
  Up / Down     tree (sidebar) navigation (was Shift+J / K)
  Ctrl+D        jump to next (newer) message containing media
  Ctrl+U        jump to prev (older) message containing media
  Ctrl+A        upload attachment (was Shift+U / Ctrl+U)
  Ctrl+O        jump to previous (last visited) channel
  Space         enter selected channel (unchanged)

Media def: any message with embeds or stickers (covers attachments,
gifs, images, video, link previews, custom stickers).

Tree toggle: when toggled off via toggle_tree, the tree pane and its
borders are removed entirely; chat/prompt/input/status collapse to
column 0. Toggling back restores the original tree_width. Mention
notifications surface in the merged title line is suppressed when
fully hidden.

Adds 5 new actions (50-54). Ctrl+D / Ctrl+U / Ctrl+O codes (4, 21,
15) collide with standard-mode delete/upload/browser, but
config.merge_keybindings dedup pulls them out of standard mode when
vim_mode is active, so only the vim bindings fire in NORMAL.

